formation criterion (BIC) or the Akaike information criterion (AIC).\n","\n","$$BIC = log(n)p-2log(L)$$\n","$$AIC = 2p-2log(L)$$\n","\n","p is the number of parameters learned by the model. L is the maximized value of the likelihood function of the model.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"0WvorQPCBkU4"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Rather than manually searching for the optimal number of clusters, it is possible to use the Bayesian Optimization implemented by the `BayesianGaussianMixture` class"],"metadata":{"id":"w4OdQcDCA1fW"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.mixture import BayesianGaussianMixture\n","\n","bgm = BayesianGaussianMixture(n_components=10, n_init=10, random_state=1)\n","bgm.fit(X)\n","bgm.weights_.round(2)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Xh5M65reA1J3","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1709531506198,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":2087,"user":{"displayName":"Ben Xue","userId":"08600776733826581408"}},"outputId":"50a094ec-5485-4f55-80a1-e78a5dd89648"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["array([0.34, 0.34, 0.32, 0.  , 0.  , 0.  , 0.  , 0.  , 0.  , 0.  ])"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":71}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Gaussian mixture models work great on clusters with ellipsoidal shapes, but if you try to fit a dataset with different shapes, you may have bad surprises."],"metadata":{"id":"J7Cf3lP_CvHk"}}]}